1
00:00:32,208 --> 00:00:33,166
[KOTAROU gasps]

2
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:39,666
[phone ringing]

3
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:40,833
[AKANE]
Kotarou?

4
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:44,250
[KOTAROU]
Uh, sorry, but you're moving?

5
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,083
[AKANE]
Yeah.

6
00:00:45,166 --> 00:00:47,208
[KOTAROU]
Where? When?

7
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:48,583
[AKANE]
Chiba, probably.

8
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:50,375
I'm looking at schools there.

9
00:00:50,458 --> 00:00:52,458
Have you ever heard of Koumei?

10
00:00:53,541 --> 00:00:55,500
[music playing]

11
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:17,125
[KOTAROU] Excuse me,
but... can you help me?

12
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:19,875
[music playing]

13
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:01,666
Oh, Akane has excellent grades.

14
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:03,125
There shouldn't be a problem.

15
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:04,083
[SAORI]
Really?

16
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:06,000
That's so wonderful to hear!

17
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:07,625
[RYOKO]
Moving must be stressful.

18
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:09,833
I heard it's because your
husband was transferred?

19
00:03:09,916 --> 00:03:12,541
[SAORI] Yes, but knowing Akane
will go to a good school

20
00:03:12,625 --> 00:03:13,875
is such a relief.

21
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:18,291
[WOMAN 10A]
Here's the application form.

22
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:22,000
[AKANE]
Thanks so much.

23
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:45,750
[KOTAROU]
Akane!

24
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:56,416
I just wanted to see you.

25
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,458
Yeah?

26
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:05,666
So, we met with Miss Ryoko.

27
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:06,750
And...?

28
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,875
I'm applying to Koumei.

29
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:11,583
With a recommendation.

30
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:21,583
[AKANE]
I'm sorry.

31
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,125
[KOTAROU]
Hm?

32
00:04:24,208 --> 00:04:26,625
Well, you know,
we'll be separated.

33
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:31,208
I'm just not sure what to do.

34
00:04:33,458 --> 00:04:34,750
[KOTAROU]
It's not your fault.

35
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:39,750
We'll be okay, even far apart.

36
00:04:42,791 --> 00:04:43,875
Yeah, you're right.

37
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:47,958
[KOTAROU] Maybe I'll apply
to the same school.

38
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:49,125
[AKANE gasps]

39
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:51,083
I don't have your grades,
but I'll try.

40
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:52,000
Seriously?

41
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,875
Yeah, though it's kinda far.

42
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,791
Isn't it over a
two-hour commute?

43
00:04:55,875 --> 00:04:57,083
[KOTAROU chuckles]

44
00:04:58,083 --> 00:05:00,291
I decided to go to your
cram school in the fall.

45
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:01,083
[KOTAROU]
Really?

46
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:02,166
Awesome!

47
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,500
Let's head back.

48
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:06,541
[AKANE]
'Kay.

49
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:09,583
[AKANE]
Isn't the festival this weekend?

50
00:05:09,666 --> 00:05:10,541
[KOTAROU]
Yep.

51
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:11,708
[AKANE]
I'll come watch!

52
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:13,875
[KOTAROU]
Okay.

53
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,625
[TAIKO CLASS 8A]
Cheers.

54
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:46,791
[PERFORMERS]
Cheers!

55
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:07,875
[PERFORMERS singing]

56
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:20,375
[PERFORMERS]
Heave ho! Heave ho!

57
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:24,750
Heave ho! Heave ho!

58
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:27,666
--Heave ho!
--[singing]

59
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,250
[STALL OWNER 10A]
Candy apples!

60
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,375
Come get your candy apples!

61
00:06:33,208 --> 00:06:34,291
[CHINATSU]
It's really busy!

62
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:35,416
[AOI]
Yeah, no joke.

63
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,416
[CHINATSU]
Where's Hira at?

64
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,625
This was his idea.

65
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:39,458
[HIRA]
Hey, there you are!

66
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,208
[CHINATSU]
About time!

67
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:42,375
[TRACK TEAM 3B]
Yeah, sorry.

68
00:06:42,458 --> 00:06:43,166
[AOI]
Let's get going.

69
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,458
[singing, chattering]

70
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:54,583
[STALL OWNER 10B]
One, two, three shoot--Ah!

71
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:56,791
You won, Akane! Yeah!

72
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,708
[STUDENT 10A]
I can't believe I missed!

73
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:00,125
[HIRA laughs]

74
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:02,333
--[CHINATSU] Delicious!
--[AOI] Free food is the best!

75
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:05,208
Hey, you guys wanna go
with us to the haunted house?

76
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:09,166
[CHINATSU]
That sounds fun!

77
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,083
[AOI] Isn't that place like,
for kids and stuff?

78
00:07:11,166 --> 00:07:14,000
Oh. I think you're just scared.

79
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:16,000
[AOI] Yeah, I'm not
gonna fall for that.

80
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:19,125
[CHINATSU screams]

81
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:21,166
[CHINATSU]
That was so horrifying!

82
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:23,791
[AOI] I'm sorry I ever
made fun of you!

83
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,791
[CHINATSU]
But I kind of wanna go again.

84
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:27,166
[AOI]
Yeah, me too!

85
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:28,708
--It was sorta fun!
--[CHINATSU] Totally!

86
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:31,041
[taiko drums, music]

87
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,041
[AKANE]
There he is!

88
00:07:42,125 --> 00:07:43,500
That must be Kotarou.

89
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:26,916
[CHINATSU]
Wasn't that Azumi?

90
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,000
[AKANE]
Yeah.

91
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,500
[AOI]
He looked pretty cool.

92
00:08:31,041 --> 00:08:32,000
Yeah.

93
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,958
[PERFORMER 10B]
Nice job, everyone.

94
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:41,916
Not too shabby.

95
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,125
[chattering, laughing]

96
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:45,916
I'm telling you, she was cute.

97
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,000
She's the one.

98
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,375
[KOTAROU]
It's so hot!

99
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,333
Hey, you looked
good up there earlier.

100
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,375
[KOTAROU chuckles]
I guess.

101
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:58,125
Wow, high standards.

102
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,708
[DAISUKE]
Oh, yeah.

103
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:04,833
Remember when we were
talking about light novels?

104
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:06,083
Yes?

105
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:08,208
[DAISUKE] I don't think
you should change it.

106
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:09,541
I'm not following.

107
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:11,750
[DAISUKE] That story you
let me read a while back?

108
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,500
It's just--I'm almost positive

109
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:15,458
it would also work
as a light novel.

110
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,666
[TAIKO CLASS 8A]
Hey! Nice work.

111
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:23,291
We have a little time
until the next parade.

112
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:25,083
Why don't you boys take a break?

113
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:26,083
Uh, 'kay.

114
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,625
Don't have too much fun.

115
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:33,833
[DAISUKE]
You heard the man.

116
00:09:51,416 --> 00:09:52,541
[CHINATSU]
Okay, hands in!

117
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:54,208
Loser takes the trash.

118
00:09:54,291 --> 00:09:55,500
[STUDENT 10A]
Right.

119
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:58,458
[ALL]
Rock, paper, scissors!

120
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:00,625
[cheering]

121
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:01,625
[TRACK TEAM 3C]
Here's your trash!

122
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:03,000
[AOI]
Don't forget this one!

123
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:09,000
[GIRL 10A] Hands down,
<i>imokoi</i> is my favorite.

124
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:11,416
[GIRL 10B]
Oh my gosh, it's mine too!

125
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,500
[AKANE]
Aw, now I want some <i>imokoi</i> .

126
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:14,291
[HIRA chuckles]

127
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:15,791
Wow, You're still hungry?

128
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:16,791
Yeah.

129
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:19,083
Jeez. You should pace yourself.

130
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:20,541
[AKANE]
No one asked you!

131
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,541
[HIRA]
Hey, Mizuno.

132
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:28,458
[AKANE]
Huh?

133
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:30,000
Come on. Wanna get some?

134
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:36,375
[AKANE]
I'm so excited.

135
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:38,375
You must be hungry, huh, Mizuno?

136
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:39,458
[AKANE]
Maybe.

137
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:58,125
[HIRA]
You look so happy.

138
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,833
It is my favorite.

139
00:11:01,916 --> 00:11:03,625
It's a Kawagoe specialty.

140
00:11:03,708 --> 00:11:06,041
Bet you'll miss it
when you move, huh?

141
00:11:06,125 --> 00:11:08,291
You don't have to
rub salt in the wound.

142
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:09,375
My bad.

143
00:11:11,416 --> 00:11:12,708
Sorry.

144
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,000
It's okay.

145
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:21,333
[HIRA] I guess it's
just... I feel weird.

146
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:25,375
When you told me that
you were moving to Chiba,

147
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:27,083
I didn't know what to do.

148
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,375
[HIRA]
I've always had a crush on you.

149
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:42,000
[HIRA] The passion you
show when you run...

150
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:43,666
You're so captivating.

151
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:02,791
Sorry.

152
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:04,791
But, look, the thing is...

153
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:06,541
I'm dating someone.

154
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:08,833
[HIRA]
I know, but still.

155
00:12:10,208 --> 00:12:11,833
Why'd you pick Azumi?

156
00:12:11,916 --> 00:12:15,166
Like, we've been on the track
club together for years!

157
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:17,250
It's just--It's not fair!

158
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:19,250
I've loved you way longer!

159
00:12:24,583 --> 00:12:27,291
[AKANE]
Listen, Hira.

160
00:12:27,375 --> 00:12:29,208
You're an important
friend to me.

161
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:32,791
But that's all.

162
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:33,833
Sorry.

163
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,791
[HIRA]
It's fine.

164
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:43,625
I just wanted to tell you.

165
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:47,375
Okay, then.

166
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:54,541
[phone chimes]

167
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:55,583
[AKANE gasps]

168
00:13:18,625 --> 00:13:20,625
There you are.
This place is huge!

169
00:13:20,708 --> 00:13:22,625
I'm so glad I get to see you.

170
00:13:22,708 --> 00:13:24,958
I told the track team
I was leaving early.

171
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,041
Is something wrong?

172
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:29,791
[KOTAROU]
Were you with Hira?

173
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:31,291
Uh, yeah.

174
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:32,625
[KOTAROU]
Just the two of you?

175
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:33,500
Yes.

176
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:35,166
We were throwing away trash.

177
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:38,291
Why do you ask?

178
00:13:40,291 --> 00:13:42,333
[AKANE] By the way,
I saw your dance earlier!

179
00:13:42,416 --> 00:13:43,125
[KOTAROU]
Hmm.

180
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:44,541
It was really impressive!

181
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,000
So how long will
you be on break?

182
00:13:49,083 --> 00:13:50,333
I don't have very long.

183
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:51,708
I have to go back soon.

184
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,000
Oh, okay.

185
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:57,625
I'm kinda hungry.

186
00:13:57,708 --> 00:14:00,166
Want some <i>imokoi</i> ?

187
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:01,666
I'm actually full.

188
00:14:06,916 --> 00:14:08,291
[PERFORMER 10I]
Hey, look who it is!

189
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:09,583
[PERFORMER 10J]
It's Kotarou.

190
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:11,166
[PERFORMER 10I]
What's up, man?

191
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,166
[PERFORMER 10K]
Looking good, buddy.

192
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,500
Who's the girl?

193
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:15,958
[KOTAROU]
None of your business.

194
00:14:16,041 --> 00:14:18,250
Jeez, what's your deal, huh?

195
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:19,750
[KOTAROU]
It's not like that.

196
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:22,125
[PERFORMER 10K]
Man, to be that young again.

197
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,750
Ha. Don't worry, we won't
tell your old man

198
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,250
about your girlfriend.

199
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,958
[PERFORMER 10K]
Come on, let's go get a drink.

200
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:34,250
Kotarou?

201
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:37,666
You're acting kinda weird.

202
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:38,833
Am I?

203
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:39,958
Are you upset?

204
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:41,041
Not really.

205
00:14:41,125 --> 00:14:41,958
See?

206
00:14:42,041 --> 00:14:43,166
I'm not upset.

207
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:45,125
Yes, you are.

208
00:14:45,208 --> 00:14:46,166
[sighs]

209
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,208
--Is it about the move?
--Not really.

210
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:50,416
So why are you angry?

211
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,166
I'm not!

212
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,208
[AKANE gasps]

213
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,541
Just let it go, already.

214
00:14:58,041 --> 00:14:59,458
I'm not angry.

215
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:02,333
Please, just tell me!

216
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:03,458
What's wrong?

217
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,458
I wanna know.

218
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:07,750
Please, Kotarou.

219
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,125
What'd I do wrong?

220
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:17,291
It's because...

221
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,625
...I saw you--

222
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:21,291
[AKANE]
Huh?

223
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:22,625
You and Hira.

224
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:29,833
[STALL OWNER 10C]
Nice throw, young man!

225
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:32,958
[AKANE]
Hey.

226
00:15:33,041 --> 00:15:35,541
Hira... confessed to me.

227
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:39,208
I turned him down, though.

228
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:45,958
[KOTAROU coughing]

229
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:47,375
[AKANE]
I'll get you some water.

230
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,000
[KOTAROU]
It's fine. [coughs]

231
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,125
I don't have time.

232
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:57,625
[KOTAROU]
I've gotta go. See ya.

233
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:32,625
--[chanting]
--[taiko drums]

234
00:16:46,916 --> 00:16:49,875
--[taiko drums]
--[music]

235
00:17:05,041 --> 00:17:07,416
[crying]

236
00:17:19,083 --> 00:17:20,625
[crying]

237
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:31,041
[crying]

238
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:05,750
[KOTAROU groans]

239
00:18:08,208 --> 00:18:09,166
[grunts]

240
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,583
[gasps]

241
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:45,125
[SETSUKO]
I keep falling asleep.

242
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:46,625
[AIRA]
Me, too.

243
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:48,583
[MIU] Studying is so boring
I can't seem to stay awake.

244
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:50,458
I just want exams
to be over already

245
00:18:50,541 --> 00:18:52,083
so I don't have to
stress about high school.

246
00:18:52,166 --> 00:18:54,958
[SETSUKO] And I'm so over
my mom nagging me.

247
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,666
[MIU] Nagging just makes
me want to study less.

248
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:57,916
[SETSUKO]
I know!

249
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,250
[MIU] Parents just don't
understand our struggle.

250
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:37,000
Okay.

251
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:44,416
That changes up
the whole equation.

252
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:45,791
So watch out for that.

253
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:04,916
[AKANE]
Excuse me, sorry to bother you.

254
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,541
Why do you have this book?

255
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:08,625
[STAFF 10A]
Oh, someone requested it.

256
00:20:35,416 --> 00:20:37,625
They said...

257
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:39,708
...someone requested
this book.

258
